ESSAYS ON MEN AND MANNERS.</P>
<P>BY WILLIAM SHENSTONE, ESQ.</P>
<P>IN ONE VOLUME.</P>
<P><Q>&startq;Every &s;ingle ob&s;ervation that is publi&s;hed by a man of ge|nius, be it ever &s;o trivial, &s;hould be e&s;teemed of im|portance; becau&s;e he &s;peaks from his own impre&s;&s;ions; whereas common men publi&s;h common things, which they perhaps gleaned from frivolous writers.&endq;</Q></P>
