<P N="1">I. THE arguments again&s;t pride drawn &s;o frequently by our clergy from the general infirmity, circum|&s;tances, and cata&s;trophe of our nature, are extremely trifling and in&s;ignificant. Man is not proud as a &s;pecies, but as an individual; not, as comparing him&s;elf with other beings, but with his fellow-creatures.</P>
