<P>The r$&s;erve or &s;hyne&s;s of men of &s;en&s;e generally con|fines them to a &s;mall acquaintance; and they find num|bers their avowed enemies, the &s;imilarity of who&s;e ta&s;tes, had fortun$ brought them once acquainted, would have rendered them their fonde&s;t friends.</P>
