<P>Be cautious not to con&s;ider a per&s;on as your &s;uperior, merely becau&s;e he is your &s;uperior in the point of a&s;&s;ur|ance. This has often depre&s;&s;ed the &s;pirit of a per&s;on of de&s;ert and diffidence.</P>
<P>A proper a&s;&s;urance, and competent fortune, are e&s;|&s;ential to liberty.</P>
